     <h4>About Clicker2Go</h4>
     <br>

       <div class="form-wrapper">
	 <div class="about-text">
          <p>
            Clicker2Go is a website/webapp designed to enhance the learning experience during and after lectures.
            Its aim is to make lectures interactive by allowing the lecturer to make multiple choice questions that
            the students can answer in real time through Clicker2Go on their laptops, tablets, or mobile phones.
	  </p>
	  
	  <p> Clicker2Go can be easily used in any learning institution without requiring the purchase of expensive hardware equipment. </p>
	  <p>  
	    Here is a list of the supported features:
	    
	    <ul>
	      <li> Create courses, lectures by date, and multiple choice questions for each lecture</li>
	      <li> CountDown Timer for each question</li>
	      <li> Statistics for each answered question</li>
	      <li> Comments after each question for explanation and discussion of the question</li>
	    </ul>
            
          </p>
	  
	  <p> Clicker2Go has been developed during course Unit COMP10120 'First Year Team project' at the School of Computer Science of the University of Manchester by a group of six students (Group X4).
	  
	  <p>The code of the project is available for free to use and modify, provided attribution is given and that it is not used (or any modified derivative) for commercial purposes.
	  </p>
	  <p>
	    For Clicker2Go we have used and included code from <a href='https://github.com/j4mie/idiorm'> Idiorm </a> library for php and mysql interaction.
	  </p>
	  </div>
      </div>

